DURBAN - Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba is trying hard to convince the international community that the country remains a strong investment destination. His comments come as South Africa grapples with downgrades from two rating agencies.READ: Gigaba commits to fiscal consolidation after downgradesThe minister was speaking at the World Economic Forum on Africa in Durban.He said the downgrades were taken seriously."We are doing all we can not to experience further downgrades and to keep investor and business confidence up," he said. eNCA